{"comments":"Symmetry Operations — Transformations that preserve symmetry.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nSymmetry operations are the actual transformations that can be applied\nto shapes while preserving their symmetry properties. This includes:\n- Identity (do nothing)\n- Reflection (mirror across axis)\n- Rotation (rotate by angle)\n- Translation (shift by vector)\n- Glide (reflect + translate)\n- Composition (combine operations)\n\n## Use Cases\n\n- Transform application\n- Operation algebra\n- Symmetry verification\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Show)\n- Geometry.Angle (Degrees)\n- Symmetry.Reflection (ReflectionAxis)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[68,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Operations.purs","start":[68,3]},"title":"Identity"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Symmetry","Reflection"],"ReflectionAxis"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[69,12],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Operations.purs","start":[69,3]},"title":"Reflect"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Angle"],"Degrees"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[70,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Operations.purs","start":[70,3]},"title":"Rotate"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[71,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Geometry/Symmetry/Operations.purs","start":[71,3]},"title":"Translate"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Geometry","Symmetry","